<title type="html"><![CDATA[SMB1: Scrolling Render Math Problem]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=4714&amp;p=41575#p41575"><![CDATA[
RenderAreaGraphics:<br />            lda CurrentColumnPos         ;store LSB of where we're at<br />            and #$01<br />            sta $05<br />            ldy VRAM_Buffer2_Offset      ;store vram buffer offset<br />            sty $00<br />            lda CurrentNTAddr_Low        ;get current name table address<br />            sta VRAM_Buffer2+1,y          ;we're supposed to render<br />            lda CurrentNTAddr_High<br />            sta VRAM_Buffer2,y<br /><strong>        lda #$9a                        ;store length byte of 26 here with d7 set<br />            sta VRAM_Buffer2+2,y    ;to increment by 32 (in columns)</strong><br />            lda #$00                        ;init attribute row<br />            sta $04<br />            tax<br /><br />Every Time I try to change it to Render using Horizontal or vertical mirroring and it does not work properly, and every<br />value I use except #$9a corrupts the screen , I even tried the Windows Calculator, It didn't work<br /><br />If you want to, I need some help on turning this routine to handle rendering for Horizontal mirroring or One screen mirroring<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=287">Hamtaro126</a> — Thu Jan 08, 2009 8:07 pm</p><hr />
